Explanation:

We use two nested loops to iterate through the string and count the occurrences of each lowercase English letter and '?' in the string. We initialize the result variable to the maximum possible integer value (INT_MAX) and update it whenever we encounter a '?'. After iterating through the entire string, we return the final result.

The time complexity is O(n) because we have a single loop for each character in the string. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single integer array to store the count of each lowercase English letter and '?'. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few simple operations and does not consume significant energy.

